extends ../layout

append styles
  style
    body {
      background-color: #fff;
      color: #333;
      font: 1em / 1.4 Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
      padding: 1em;
      margin: 0;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

block content
  h2 Styling Basics
  section
    h3 Task 1
    blockquote(cite="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Forms/Test_your_skills:_Styling_basics#Styling_basics_1")
      p Our basic form styling assessment is fairly free-form, and you have a lot of flexibility over what you end up doing here. But your CSS should aim to fulfill the following requirements:
      ol 
        li Add some kind of lightweight "reset" to make fonts, padding, margin, and sizing more consistent to begin with.
        li On top of that, add in some nice, consistent styling for the inputs and button.
        li Use some kind of layout technique to make the inputs and labels line up neatly.
    form
      h2 Edit your preferences
      ul 
        li 
          label(for="e-mail") Email:
          input#e-mail(type="email" name="e-mail")
        li 
          label(for="website") Website:
          input#website(type="url" name="website")
        li 
          label(for="phone") Phone number:
          input#phone(type="tel" name="phone")
        li 
          label(for="food") Favorite food:
          select#food(name="food")
            option Salad
            option Curry
            option Pizza
            option Fajitas
        li 
          button(type="submit") Update preferences
